        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>St. Louis, Mo.</placeName>
                <date>Decbr 8<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 5613.<add>1852</add></date>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir!</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">After receipt of your favor, dated <date>Oct 17th</date>,<lb/> I
                applied to Adams Express and got your package.—<lb/> But as I told you already in my
                last it is of no use<lb/> to that congregation any more and I doubt almost
                    <sic>wether</sic><lb/> it would have been under any circumstances whatever;
                but<lb/> this is certainly none of your fault, however a proof more of<lb/> the lack
                of zeal and interest which our coreligionarics feel<lb/> in promoting Judaism, in
                helping to erect houses of worship<lb/> and so on;—But do you believe, dear Sir!
                That you will revive<lb/> Judaism and better the existing state of things by
                articles as the one<lb/> „what can be done” in your Occident No. 116.?—</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I wished to God almighty for the sake of our holy his defaced<lb/>
                and forsaken religion, you would have the strength and courage<lb/> to breake the
                crust. that Rabbanism, fanaticism, hypocrisy and<lb/> Ignorance have laid around our
                Religion so that the Law<lb/> of <persName>Moshe</persName> and the
                    <sic>Profets</sic> is forgotten for the abuses of middle-age<lb/> and
                    <del>that</del> through which the true heavenly light of our <add>תורה</add>
                <add>?</add>can hardly penetrate.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">While on the one hand you translate the divine scriptures<lb/> on
                the other hand you foster their misunderstanding and misinterpreting<lb/> by
                articles like that „what can be done”!</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Excuse my sincerity—and if our views differ, believe me that<lb/> I
                know to respect difference of opinion, though I would heartily<lb/> lament it in so
                far as I feel it injures the cause, for which in<lb/> principle we feel alike, and
                which I only wish and hope to see<lb/> promoted and fostered by you.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I succeeded at last with some friends of the cause to write<lb/> two
                congregations here, the Imanu El and Bne Brith<hi rend="sup">x</hi>—The new
                congregation<lb/> is about to organize under the s<add>?</add> and title <hi
                    rend="underline">„Bne-El”</hi>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I am at work to make the outlines of a constitution, a<lb/> copy of
                which I will send you as soon as adopted.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Our means in cash on hand and Real Estate amount now<lb/> to more
                than two Thousand dollars, and I hope that at your<lb/> next visit to <placeName>St
                    Louis</placeName> we will be able to hear you in our<lb/> new house of Prayer
                and give you a better, a heartfelt and<lb/>
                <sic>thankfull</sic> welcome.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Enclosed you will find $5.00<lb/>00 for advertisement and
                circulars<lb/> of the late Bne Brith Congr. and I will try to make the Bne El<lb/>
                better patrons of your Occident.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">with sincere respect your affectionate</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">
                <persName role="author">Isidor Bush</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="The following is written sideways near the bottom of the left side of the page"
                    ><hi rend="sup">x</hi>
                <sic>comonly</sic> called Bavarian and Bohemian Congr.</p>
            <pb n="2V"/>
            <p rend="indent(5)">
                <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">Editor Occident</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">
                <placeName>Philada.</placeName>
            </p>
